            {
                "comment_id": 1,
                "post_id": 1,
                "user_id": 1,
                "content": "As a first-time buyer saving for a small apartment, this update makes me a bit nervous. Does the 8% QoQ dip in prime spill over into more affordable areas (JVC, IMPZ, Town Square), or is it mostly affecting high-end? With DLD volumes down 22%, are sellers more open to negotiation now, or are listings just pulling back? \n\nAre banks tightening mortgage approvals because of this \"risk-off\" mood? I\u2019m debating whether to lock a fixed rate now or wait 3\u20136 months. Any data on mid-market prices vs rents in Q1 would really help. I don\u2019t want to catch a falling knife, but I\u2019m also worried rents will keep climbing. \n\nFor first-time buyers, what should we be watching most right now\u2014service charges, developer incentives/payment plans, or off-plan risks? Would appreciate insights from agents/analysts.",
                "created_at": "2026-04-27 07:43:41.718380",
                "score": 0
