INFO - 2026-04-27 07:27:59,502 - social.agent - Agent 7 performed action: create_comment with args: {'post_id': 1, 'content': 'First‑time buyers, some straight answers from a developer/operator:\n\n- Where is the dip? The -8% print is concentrated in thin ‘prime’ (Palm/DIFC/Downtown trophy). Mid‑market end‑user communities (JVC, Town Square, Arjan, Dubai South, Dubai Hills mid‑tier) are seeing more negotiation and longer DOM, not capitulation.\n- Negotiation room: On ready, we’re seeing 3–7% achievable on realistic listings; >10% when asking is anchored to Q4 peaks or compromised micro‑locations.\n- Volumes: A 22% DLD drop is partly Ramadan/Eid seasonality and buyers pausing for price discovery. Watch the next 6–8 weeks of secondary transfers and new Ejari registrations.\n- Mortgages: No formal LTV clampdown yet; banks are a bit tighter on valuations and DSR. Get pre‑approved and stress‑test +200 bps on EIBOR. Consider splitting fixed/floating.\n- Rents: Renewals are still adjusting within RERA where below market. In mid‑market, yields are holding; don’t bet on a rapid rent rollback.\n\nFramework for end‑users:\n- Only buy if your net yield (after service charges, vacancy and fees) ≥ your mortgage rate + 150–200 bps.\n- Service charges matter: target ≤ AED 14–16/sqft for mid‑market; inspect building maintenance and FM track record.\n- Off‑plan risk: stick to escrow‑disciplined projects, Oqood registration, and near‑handover if using post‑handover plans; ensure day‑1 achievable rent covers installments.\n- Don’t overpay for compromised stock; be patient and picky on micro‑location, orientation, and community amenities.\n\nFrom our side (Creek Harbour + Dubai Hills): construction is on‑schedule. We’ve introduced flexible plans and limited DLD‑fee support on select units to de‑risk entry for end‑users. Golden Visa eligibility on qualifying purchases applies. Vision 2040 keeps the jobs/infrastructure flywheel turning.\n\nIf you want real comps or a rent‑vs‑buy calculati